import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from statsmodels.tsa.seasonal import seasonal_decompose
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

from sklearn.model_selection import TimeSeriesSplit, cross_val_score
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error

from catboost import CatBoostRegressor
import optuna

# For cyclic features
def fourier_ext(df, col, period):
    df[col+'_sin'] = np.sin(2 * np.pi * df[col]/period) 
    df[col+'_cos'] = np.cos(2 * np.pi * df[col]/period)
    
    return df

def time_converter(df, column):
    df[column] = pd.to_datetime(df[column])
    
    df["day"] = df[column].dt.day
    df["month"] = df[column].dt.month
    df["year"] = df[column].dt.year
    df["weekno"] = df[column].dt.weekday
    df["day_of_year"] = df[column].dt.day_of_year
    df["week_of_year"] = df[column].dt.weekofyear
    
    return df

df = pd.read_csv("Swing Days.csv")
df = time_converter(df, "Swings")


df["temp"] = 1

df["swing_count_per_year"] = df.groupby(["year"])["temp"].transform("cumsum")
df["swing_count_per_month"] = df.groupby(["month"])["temp"].transform("cumsum")
df["swing_count_per_monthofyear"] = df.groupby(["year","month"])["temp"].transform("cumsum")
df["swing_count_per_day"] = df.groupby(["day"])["temp"].transform("cumsum")
df["swing_count_per_weekno"] = df.groupby(["weekno"])["temp"].transform("cumsum")
df["swing_count_per_dayofyear"] = df.groupby(["day_of_year"])["temp"].transform("cumsum")
df["swing_count_per_weekofyear"] = df.groupby(["week_of_year"])["temp"].transform("cumsum")

df = df.drop(["temp"],1)

df.loc[df.weekno== 0,"day_name"] = "Monday"
df.loc[df.weekno== 1,"day_name"] = "Tuesday"
df.loc[df.weekno== 2,"day_name"] = "Wednesday"
df.loc[df.weekno== 3,"day_name"] = "Thursday"
df.loc[df.weekno== 4,"day_name"] = "Friday"
df = df.drop(["weekno"],1)
df = df.rename(columns = {"Days between prev swing" : "days_between_prev_swing"})


df["prev_swing_shifted1"] = df.days_between_prev_swing.shift(1)
df = df[1:]

df = df.sort_values(["year","day_of_year"])

import lightgbm as lgbm
best = 13.726978298033076
for i in df.columns:
    if i in ["days_between_prev_swing", "Swings"]:
        continue
    else:      
        model = lgbm.LGBMRegressor()
        X = df.drop(["days_between_prev_swing", "Swings", i],1)
        y = df["days_between_prev_swing"]

        from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
        X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size = .19, random_state = 42)
        model.fit(X_train, y_train)

        preds = model.predict(X_test)
        from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error

        print(mean_squared_error(y_test, preds, squared = False))
        real = pd.DataFrame(y_test)
        real["preds"] = preds
        print("Daily average error is >>> {}".format(np.mean(abs(real.days_between_prev_swing - real.preds))))
        
        val = np.mean(abs(real.days_between_prev_swing - real.preds))
        if val <= best:
            best = val
            df.drop([i],1, inplace = True)
            print(i, "  dropped")
        else:
            print(i, "  not dropped")

The value of lower bound is: 74

In [127]:
def objective(trial,data= df,target = df["days_between_prev_swing"]):   
    data = data.drop(["days_between_prev_swing"],1)
    
    params = {
        'max_depth': trial.suggest_int('max_depth', 6, 10),
        'learning_rate': trial.suggest_categorical('learning_rate', [0.005, 0.02, 0.05, 0.08, 0.1]),
        'n_estimators': trial.suggest_int('n_estimators', 2000, 8000),
        'max_bin': trial.suggest_int('max_bin', 200, 400),
        'min_data_in_leaf': trial.suggest_int('min_data_in_leaf', 1, 300),
        'l2_leaf_reg': trial.suggest_float('l2_leaf_reg', 0.0001, 1.0, log = True),
        'subsample': trial.suggest_float('subsample', 0.1, 0.8),
        'random_seed': 42,
        'loss_function': 'RMSE',
        'verbose': False
    }
    
    tscv_splits = list(tscv.split(data,target))
    
    rms_errs = []
    
    for split_train, split_val in tscv_splits:
        train_x, train_y = data.iloc[split_train], target.iloc[split_train]
        test_x, test_y = data.iloc[split_val], target.iloc[split_val]
        
        model = CatBoostRegressor(**params)  
        model.fit(train_x, train_y, verbose = False)
        preds = model.predict(test_x)
        rms = mean_squared_error(test_y, preds, squared=False)
        rms_errs.append(rms)
        
    return np.mean(rms_errs)

if TUNE:
    study = optuna.create_study(direction = 'minimize')
    study.optimize(objective, n_trials = 5)
    print('Best value:', study.best_value)

def get_cv_result(model):
    cv_result = cross_val_score(model, df.drop(["days_between_prev_swing"],1) , df["days_between_prev_swing"],
                                cv=tscv, scoring="neg_root_mean_squared_error",
                                verbose=2)
    print(-cv_result)
    print("RMSE: %0.2f (+/- %0.2f)" % (-cv_result.mean(), cv_result.std()))
    return model

def objective(trial,data = df,target = data["days_between_prev_swing"]):   
    data = data.drop(["days_between_prev_swing"],1)
    
    params = {
        "objective" : "regression",
   "lambda_l1": trial.suggest_float("lambda_l1", 1e-8, 10.0, log=True),
        "lambda_l2": trial.suggest_float("lambda_l2", 1e-8, 10.0, log=True),
        "num_leaves": trial.suggest_int("num_leaves", 2, 256),
        "feature_fraction": trial.suggest_float("feature_fraction", 0.4, 1.0),
        "bagging_fraction": trial.suggest_float("bagging_fraction", 0.4, 1.0),
        "bagging_freq": trial.suggest_int("bagging_freq", 1, 7),
        "min_child_samples": trial.suggest_int("min_child_samples", 5, 100),
    }
    
    tscv_splits = list(tscv.split(data,target))
    
    rms_errs = []
    
    for split_train, split_val in tscv_splits:
        train_x, train_y = data.iloc[split_train], target.iloc[split_train]
        test_x, test_y = data.iloc[split_val], target.iloc[split_val]
        
        model = lgbm.LGBMRegressor(**params)  
        model.fit(train_x, train_y, verbose = False)
        preds = model.predict(test_x)
        rms = mean_squared_error(test_y, preds, squared=False)
        rms_errs.append(rms)
        
    return np.mean(rms_errs)

if TUNE:
    study = optuna.create_study(direction = 'minimize')
    study.optimize(objective, n_trials = 75)
    print('Best value:', study.best_value)

tscv_splits = list(tscv.split(df.drop(["days_between_prev_swing"],1),data["days_between_prev_swing"]))
target = data["days_between_prev_swing"]
rms_errs = []
abs_diff = []

from sklearn.linear_model import ElasticNet
for split_train, split_val in tscv_splits:
    train_x, train_y = data.iloc[split_train], target.iloc[split_train]
    test_x, test_y = data.iloc[split_val], target.iloc[split_val]
    print(test_x.shape)

    model = lgbm.LGBMRegressor(**lgbm_params)  
    model.fit(train_x, train_y, verbose = False)
    preds = model.predict(test_x)
    
    model2 = CatBoostRegressor(**cat_params)
    model2.fit(train_x, train_y, verbose = False)
    preds2 = model2.predict(test_x)
    
    regr = ElasticNet(random_state=0).fit(train_x, train_y)
    preds3 = regr.predict(test_x)
    
    abs_diff.append(abs(test_y - ((preds + preds2 + preds3)/3)))
    rms = mean_squared_error(test_y, (preds+preds2 + preds3)/3, squared=False)
    rms_errs.append(rms)
